Description:
The Senior Business Intelligence Analyst is responsible for the first tier of support for user requests for user administration, enhancement requests, production incidents or outages related to Business Intelligence solutions owned by the CBA organization. This role will be involved in operational improvement projects, infrastructure and vendor product deployment projects, and development of BI solutions. In addition, under the supervision of the Manager-Business Intelligence, the Senior Business Intelligence Analyst will:
Analyze, develop and enhance Bl and ETL processes that reflect best practices for error handling, operations logging and alerting, scheduling and job control;
Monitor production solutions and where necessary, perform manual procedures;
Prepare and update design specifications and operations documentation for BI solutions promoted to the production environment;
Test, maintain, and monitor production solutions and, where necessary, perform required manual procedures;
Perform user and tool administration within BI tools as requested and approved;
Troubleshoot system malfunctions and incidents surrounding supported solutions;
Coordinate with infrastructure team on maintenance of hardware, upgrades, database administration/tuning, etc. of the EDW/BI environment;
Install and test software patches/upgrades and test operating system, hardware, and database patches/upgrades installed by system administrators;
Manage work queue of incidents and user requests within Service Management application;
Identify improvements to operational processes and leads projects to implement such improvements, applying solid project management skills, team/user communications, etc;
Understand and apply HIPAA standards and regulations to all areas of work.

Requirements: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Management Information Systems, or a related business field. Four (4) years of experience with design and development of Bl solutions and/or administration of BI tools including at least two (2) years of experience with SQL.
Qualifications:
Special Requirements: Requires experience in Oracle or SQL Server environment and creation of database objects; Data Warehousing and ETL; Experience delivering high quality Reporting & Analytics solutions; Windows Server management or coordination; and troubleshooting and performing root cause analysis of IT issues. In addition, the applicant will have experience: Delivering reporting and analytics solutions; With SAP BusinessObjects: BusinessObjects Enterprise (BOE), Web Intelligence, Crystal Reports, Xcelsius, BusinessObjects Data Services, CMC, SDK; QlikView; Microsoft SQL Server: SQL Server, SSIS, Management Studio, Team Foundation Services (TFS); Oracle: Oracle RDMS10/11, Oracle Client Remedy/ITSM Service Management application; Windows Server Management or coordination with Windows administrators to investigate/resolve incidents, implement Windows patches, monitor hardware utilization, and perform hardware migrations/upgrades; and Utilize performance tuning utilities. Part-time telecommuting may be available, subject to manager's approval and business needs. All SHC positions require drug/background screening.

Qualified Candidates: Send resume to Susan Lee, Talent Acquisition Coordinator, Stanford Health Care Human Resources, 1850 Embarcadero Rd. Ste. B, Palo Alto, CA 94303. Principals Only. No phone calls. Must have unrestricted authorization to work in the US. Equal Opportunity employer.

Fueled by a dedicated workforce, Ameresco is an innovative technology company specializing in energy solutions. Customers benefit from our ability to design, develop, finance and construct solutions to increase energy efficiency, optimize operations, leverage renewable energy assets, and plan for a resilient future. Our unique position enables us to deliver objective solutions for measurable cost savings and sustainable roadmaps for energy generation. Drawing from decades of experience, Ameresco develops tailored energy projects for the commercial, industrial, government, education, healthcare and public housing sectors.
Applied Energy Group (AEG), a division of Ameresco, is seeking a Business Analyst to join the Project Services team within the VisionDSM IT Software as a Service Group. This position requires knowledge of utility energy efficiency programs, consulting experience, an understanding of the SDLC, and task management. The Business Analyst will work with Lead Business Analysts and/or Project Managers to support the delivery of medium to large size Energy Efficiency IT projects, to include requirements gathering and data analysis to support the configuration and maintenance of our proprietary tracking and analytics platform for our clients.
Collaborate with Project Managers, Lead. Business Analyst and/or clients to help define system requirements and design approach;
Enter support requests;
Perform minimal acceptance testing activities;
Support users through training, as well as provide one-on-one technical assistance;
Support User Acceptance Testing (UAT) activities;
Develop an understanding of the client processes and procedures and assist with making recommendations on appropriate configuration;
Work with Project Manager or Lead BA to define tasks and estimates for project plan;
Facilitate meetings both in-person and on the phone;
Generate requirements specifications, use cases, process flow diagrams, user interface designs, and other system documentation;
Translate business requirements into technical requirements;
Coordinate project tasks across multiple resources; and,
Identify new opportunities
